body:
I tried this code:

```rust
struct Foo {
    value: String,
}

impl Foo {

    #[cfg(not(target_os = "macos"))]
    fn not_macos(&mut self) {
        self.value.push_str(".not macOS.")
    }

    #[cfg(not(target_os = "linux"))]
    fn not_linux(&mut self) {
        self.value.push_str(".not linux.")
    }

    pub fn call(&mut self) -> String {

        if cfg!(not(target_os = "macos")) {
            self.not_macos();
        }

        if cfg!(not(target_os = "linux")) {
            self.not_linux();
        }

        self.value.clone()
    }
}

fn main() {
    println!("start");

    if cfg!(not(target_os = "macos")) {
        println!("not macOS");
    }

    if cfg!(not(target_os = "linux")) {
        println!("not Linux");
    }

    let mut foo = Foo { value: "str".to_string() };

    println!("> {}", foo.call());

    println!("end");
}
```

I expected to see this compiles and if execute returns:
```
start
not macOS
> str.not macOS.
end
```

Instead, this can't be compiled:
```
Compiling playground v0.0.1 (/playground)
error[[E0599]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/error-index.html#E0599): no method named `not_linux` found for mutable reference `&mut Foo` in the current scope
  --> src/main.rs:24:18
   |
24 |             self.not_linux();
   |                  ^^^^^^^^^ method not found in `&mut Foo`

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0599`.
error: could not compile `playground` due to previous error
```

